 of the worlds seven oil and gas supermajors whose performance in  made it the worlds sixthlargest oil and gas company the sixthlargest energy company by market capitalization and the company with the worlds fifthlargest revenue turnover it is a vertically integrated company operating in all areas of the oil and gas industry including exploration and production refining distribution and marketing petrochemicals power generation and trading it also has renewable energy interests in biofuels and wind power as of  december  bp had operations in  countries worldwide produced around  million barrels per day  md of oil equivalent and had total proved reserves of  billion barrels × m of oil equivalent the company has around  service stations worldwide its largest division is bp america in the united states in russia bp owns a  stake in rosneft the worlds largest publicly traded oil and gas company by hydrocarbon reserves and production bp has a primary listing on the london stock exchange and is a constituent of the ftse  index it has secondary listings on the frankfurt stock exchange and the new york stock exchange bps origins date back to the founding of the anglopersian oil company in  established as a subsidiary of burmah oil company to exploit oil discoveries in iran in  it became the angloiranian oil company and in  british petroleum in  the company expanded beyond the middle east to alaska and it was one of the first companies to strike oil in the north sea british petroleum acquired majority control of standard oil of ohio in  formerly majority stateowned the british government privatised the company in stages between  and  british petroleum merged with amoco in  becoming bp amoco plc and acquired arco and burmah castrol in  becoming bp plc in  from  to  bp was a partner in the tnkbp joint venture in russia bp has been directly involved in several major environmental and safety incidents among them were the  texas city refinery explosion which caused the death of  workers and resulted in a recordsetting osha fine britains largest oil spill the wreck of torrey canyon and the  prudhoe bay oil spill the largest oil spill on alaskas north slope which resulted in a us million civil penalty the largest perbarrel penalty at that time for an oil spill the  deepwater horizon oil spill the largest accidental release of oil into marine waters in history resulted in severe environmental health and economic consequences and serious legal and public relations repercussions for bp  million gallons of corexit oil dispersant were used in the cleanup response becoming the largest application of such chemicals in us history the company pleaded guilty to  counts of felony manslaughter two misdemeanors one felony count of lying to congress and agreed to pay more than  billion in fines and penalties the largest criminal resolution in us history on july   bp and five states announced an  billion settlement to be used for clean water act penalties and various claims contents  history   to    to    to    to    to present  operations  operations by location  united kingdom  united states  other locations  main business segments  oil and natural gas  oil refining and marketing  alternative and low carbon energy  corporate affairs  stock  branding and public relations  environmental record  position on global warming  hazardous substance dumping –  air pollution violations  colombian farmland damages claim  canadian oil sands  health and safety violations   sea gem offshore oil rig disaster  texas city refinery explosion and leaks   explosion   toxic substance release   chemical leak  prudhoe bay   caspian sea gas leak and blowout  california storage tanks  deepwater horizon explosion and oil spill  environmental impact  effects on human health  criminal prosecutions  justice department suit  civil proceedings and claims settlement  political influence  release of lockerbie bomber  political contributions and lobbying  market manipulation investigations