he local marketing companies in several european countries refineries were built in llandarcy in wales the first refinery in the united kingdom and grangemouth in scotland it also acquired the controlling stake in the courchelettes refinery in france and formed with the government of australia a partnership named commonwealth oil refineries which built the australians first refinery in laverton victoria in  burmah employed winston churchill as a paid consultant to lobby the british government to allow apoc have exclusive rights to persian oil resources which were subsequently granted by the iranian monarchy apoc and the armenian businessman calouste gulbenkian were the driving forces behind the creation of turkish petroleum company tpc in  to explore oil in mesopotamia now iraq and by  apoc held  of tpc shares in  tpc received concession in the mesopotamian oil resources from the iraqi government under british mandate tpc finally struck oil in iraq on  october  by  the apocs shareholding in tpc which by now was named iraq petroleum company ipc was reduced to  as the result of the changing geopolitics post ottoman empire breakup and the red line agreement relations were generally cordial between the prowest hashemite monarchy – in iraq and ipc in spite of disputes centered on iraqs wish for greater involvement and more royalties during the – time period ipc monopolised oil exploration inside the red line excluding saudi arabia and bahrain in  burmah oil and royal dutch shell formed the joint marketing company burmahshell in  apoc and shell formed the consolidated petroleum company for sale and marketing in cyprus south africa and ceylon which in  followed by a joint marketing company shellmex and bp in the united kingdom in  aioc and shell formed the shelldarcy exploration partners partnership to explore for oil in nigeria the partnership was equally owned but operated by shell it was later replaced by shelldarcy petroleum development company and shellbp petroleum development company now shell petroleum development company in  apoc and gulf oil founded the kuwait oil company as an equally owned partnership the oil concession rights were awarded to the company on  december  and the company started drilling operations in  in  rezā shāh requested the international community to refer to persia as iran which was reflected in the name change of apoc to the angloiranian oil company aioc in  british petroleum chemicals was incorporated as a joint venture of aioc and the distillers company in  the company was renamed british hydrocarbon chemicals following world war ii nationalistic sentiments were on the rise in the middle east most notable being iranian nationalism and arab nationalism in iran the aioc and the prowestern iranian government led by prime minister ali razmara resisted nationalist calls to revise aiocs concession terms in irans favour in march  razmara was assassinated and mohammed mossadeq a nationalist was elected as the new prime minister by the majlis of iran parliament in april  the iranian government nationalised the iranian oil industry by unanimous vote and the national iranian oil company nioc was formed displacing the aioc the aioc withdrew its management from iran and britain organized an effective worldwide embargo of iranian oil the british government which owned the aioc contested the nationalisation at the international court of justice at the hague but its complaint was dismissed prime minister churchill asked president eisenhower for help in overthrowing mossadeq the antimossadeq plan was orchestrated under the codename operation ajax by cia and operation boot by sis mi the cia and the british helped stage a coup in august  the  iranian coup détat which established prowestern general fazlollah zahedi as the new pm and greatly strengthened the political power of shah mohammad reza pahlavi the aioc was able to return to iran  to edit a bp truck from  in  the aioc became the british petroleum company after the  iranian coup détat iranian oil participants ltd iop a holding company was founded in october  in london to bring iranian oil back to the international market british petroleum was a founding member of this company with  stake iop operated and managed oil facilities in iran on behalf of nioc similar to the saudiaramco  agreement of  the consortium agreed to share profits on a – basis with iran but not to open its books to iranian auditors or to allow iranians onto its board of directors in  british petroleum entered the canadian market through the purchase of a minority stake in calgarybased triad oil company and expanded further to alaska in  resulting discovery of oil at prudhoe bay in  in  its subsidiary darcy exploration co africa ltd has been granted four oil concessions in libya in  scottish oils ceased oilshale operations in  it was the first company to strike oil in the north sea in  bp entered the united states by acquiring the east coast refining and marketing assets of sinclair oil corporation the canadian holding company of british petroleum was renamed bp canada in  and in  it acquired  stake of supertest petroleum by the s british petroleum had developed a reputation for taking on the riskiest ventures it earned the company massive profits it also earned them the worst safety record in the industry in  the giant oil tanker torrey canyon foundered off the english coast over  million gallons of crude oil was spilled into the atlantic and onto the beaches of cornwall and brittany causing britains worstever oil spill the ship was owned by the bahamasbased barracuda tanker corporation and was flying the flag of liberia a wellknown flag of convenience but was being chartered by british petroleum the ship was bombed by raf jet bombers in an effort to break up the ship and burn off the leaking oil but this failed to destroy the oil slick in  bp acquired chemical and platic assets of the distillers company which were merged with british hydrocarbon chemicals